In [68]:
TN=cnf_matrix[0][0]
FN=cnf_matrix[1][0]
TP=cnf_matrix[1][1]
FP=cnf_matrix[0][1]
# Sensitivity, hit rate, recall, or true positive rate
TPR = TP/(TP+FN)
# Specificity or true negative rate
TNR = TN/(TN+FP) 
# Precision or positive predictive value
PPV = TP/(TP+FP)
# Fall out or false positive rate
FPR = FP/(FP+TN)
# False negative rate
FNR = FN/(TP+FN)
#recall
RCC=TP/(TP+FN)
#F1_score
FSC=2*(PPV*RCC)/(PPV+RCC)
# Overall accuracy
ACC = (TP+TN)/(TP+FP+FN+TN)
In [69]:
print("True positive rate :",TPR)
print("True negative rate:",TNR)
print("False positive rate:",FPR)
print("False negative rate:",FNR)
print("Precision :",PPV)
print("recall :",RCC)
print("F1_score :",FSC)
print("Accuracy :",ACC)

from sklearn.metrics import roc_curve
from sklearn.metrics import auc

fpr, tpr, thresholds = roc_curve(y_test, y_pred_log)

fpr2, tpr2, thresholds2 = roc_curve(y_test, y_pred_KNN)

fpr3, tpr3, thresholds3 = roc_curve(y_test, y_pred_dec)

fpr4, tpr4, thresholds4 = roc_curve(y_test, y_pred_NB)

fpr5, tpr5, thresholds5 = roc_curve(y_test, y_pred_LSVM)

fpr6, tpr6, thresholds6 = roc_curve(y_test, y_pred_RSVM)

fpr7, tpr7, thresholds7 = roc_curve(y_test, y_pred_RF)

roc_auc = auc(fpr, tpr)
roc_auc2 = auc(fpr2, tpr2)
roc_auc3 = auc(fpr3, tpr3)
roc_auc4 = auc(fpr4, tpr4)
roc_auc5 = auc(fpr5, tpr5)

roc_auc7 = auc(fpr7, tpr7)
